## Remarks  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  [!INCLUDE[DeprecatedContent](~/includes/deprecatedcontent-md.md)]  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="90352-103"><xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 是工作流的基本构造块。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-103">An <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> is the fundamental building block of workflows.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-104"><xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 像任意类那样定义一组属性和事件，并定义执行逻辑，这些执行逻辑定义活动的运行时行为。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-104">An <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> defines a set of properties and events, such as any class, along with execution logic that defines the activity's run-time behavior.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-105">一组可以与 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 关联的附加组件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-105">A set of additional components can be associated with an <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-106">这些组件包括但不限于验证程序、代码生成器、自定义序列化程序和设计器。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-106">These include, but are not limited to a validator, a code generator, custom serializers, and a designer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="90352-107">所有活动共享一组在 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 基类上定义的通用属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-107">All activities share a common set of properties defined on the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> base class.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="90352-108">每个 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 都可以按照需要，通过扩展此类来声明各自的附加属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-108">Each <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> can declare its own additional properties according to its requirements by extending this class.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="90352-109">因为 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 派生自 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.DependencyObject>，所以属性可以定义为标准 CLR 属性和依赖项属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-109">Because <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> derives from <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.DependencyObject>, properties can be defined as standard CLR properties and as dependency properties.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="90352-110"><xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 的执行逻辑满足在任意 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 和工作流运行时之间存在的协定。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-110">The execution logic of an <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> fulfills a contract that exists between any <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> and the workflow runtime.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-111">您必须在文档中按照功能记录任何 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 的执行逻辑，便于使用 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 的工作流开发人员了解其行为。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-111">You must document the execution logic of any <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> in a functional sense, so that a workflow developer who uses the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> knows how it behaves.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-112">对于在工作流中包括活动的工作流开发人员，执行逻辑本身是不可见的，因为执行逻辑是在工作流运行时和 <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity> 之间严格存在的协定的一部分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-112">The execution logic itself is hidden from the workflow developer who includes the activity in a workflow, because the execution logic is part of a contract that exists strictly between the workflow runtime and the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Activity>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="90352-113">此示例定义用于发送电子邮件的活动。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-113">This example defines an activity whose purpose is to send an email.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-114">该活动定义一个在相应实现中使用依赖项属性的 `Subject` 属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-114">The activity defines one property, `Subject`, that uses a dependency property in its implementation.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-115">可以采用类似的方法定义其他属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-115">Other properties can be defined in a similar way.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-116">对 `Execute` 方法进行重写，以提供用于发送电子邮件的逻辑。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-116">The `Execute` method is overridden to provide the logic for sending the email.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90352-117">有关完整示例，请参阅[发送电子邮件活动示例](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/bfb5939e-60a9-4037-af4e-2cea9e654669)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90352-117">For a complete example, see the [Send Email Activity Sample](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/bfb5939e-60a9-4037-af4e-2cea9e654669).</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public class SendEmail : Activity  
{  
    public static readonly DependencyProperty SubjectProperty =  
        DependencyProperty.Register("Subject", typeof(string), typeof(SendEmail));  
  
    public string Subject  
    {  
        get { return base.GetValue(SubjectProperty) as string; }  
        set { base.SetValue(SubjectProperty, value); }  
    }  
  
    // Define other properties...  
  
    protected override ActivityExecutionStatus Execute(ActivityExecutionContext executionContext)  
    {  
        // Logic to send the email goes here...  
        return ActivityExecutionStatus.Closed;  
    }  
}  
```

